	<div class="col-lg-7">
	<div class="content-panel pn">
<h3> Disease Ecology </h3>
<p> The majority of my research experience is on the ecology of infectious disease, using a Daphnia-microparasite interaction as a model system to test epidemiological and ecological theory. This system is ideal, as the host is clonal (i.e., no genetic nonsense unless I want it there), fast-reproducing, and perfectly sized (i.e., hundreds upon hundereds can coexist in a few liters of water). Current investigations with this system are exploring the impact of interspecific competition on epidemic dynamics, temperature variability as an infection driver, and the relative impact of pathogen exposure on fitness of different host species (i.e., "costs of resistance") </p>

</div>
</div>
</div>

<! --  Panel -->
				<div class="row">
